text: Kratié is a province in Cambodia. The capital city is also named Kratié. The province is also called Kraches or Kracheh . The Mekong River flows from the north to the south of the province. About 140 km of the river is in Kratié. The river is home to Irrawaddy dolphins as well as fish and birds. There are 5 districts and 1 municipality: *Chhloung *Chitr Borie *Kratié Municipality *Prek Prasab *Sambour *Snuol Category:1907 establishments in Asia
title: Kratié province
